1
00:00:32,333 --> 00:00:34,250
- ( theme music playing )

2
00:00:38,958 --> 00:00:40,833
- ( singing in Japanese )

3
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:12,750
- I HAVE ALL THE INGREDIENTS
I NEED FOR DINNER.

4
00:02:12,833 --> 00:02:14,333
AND NOW--

5
00:02:14,416 --> 00:02:16,416
( slightly gasps )

6
00:02:20,958 --> 00:02:22,750
- ( birds chirping )

7
00:02:22,833 --> 00:02:24,583
HOW BEAUTIFUL.

8
00:02:25,833 --> 00:02:28,708
A RESORT, HUH?

9
00:02:28,791 --> 00:02:31,666
I'D LIKE TO WITH
KAORU-SAMA SOMEDAY.

10
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:34,333
IF ONLY I COULD SEE
SUCH BEAUTIFUL SCENERY

11
00:02:34,416 --> 00:02:35,625
TOGETHER WITH HIM.

12
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:47,541
( sighs )

13
00:02:47,625 --> 00:02:48,875
WHAT IN THE WORLD WAS GOING

14
00:02:48,958 --> 00:02:51,041
THROUGH MY HEAD BACK THEN?

15
00:02:51,125 --> 00:02:53,000
BRINGING THESE FLYERS
WITH ME.

16
00:02:54,125 --> 00:02:55,166
BUT...

17
00:02:55,250 --> 00:02:58,708
BUT STILL,
WE WILL GO TOGETHER ONE DAY.

18
00:02:58,791 --> 00:03:00,083
I'M SURE.

19
00:03:00,166 --> 00:03:02,416
- Tina: WELL, WE JUST
HAVE TO INVITE THE LANDLORD

20
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:03,750
AND THE MANAGER TOO.

21
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:05,000
- Man: YEAH, GOOD IDEA.

22
00:03:05,083 --> 00:03:06,166
- AFTER ALL, THE MORE
THE MERRIER, RIGHT?

23
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:07,916
- ( gasps )
OH, MY--

24
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,750
- WE'RE BACK, AOI-CHAN.

25
00:03:09,833 --> 00:03:12,250
- UH, OH, HI.
WELCOME BACK, EVERYBODY.

26
00:03:12,333 --> 00:03:14,416
YOU ALL CAME BACK
RATHER EARLY.

27
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:16,583
- YEAH, WELL, ALL THREE OF US
JUST HAPPENED TO HAVE

28
00:03:16,666 --> 00:03:18,916
ALL OF OUR AFTERNOON CLASSES
CANCELLED.

29
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,750
- MISS LANDLORD, COME WITH US.

30
00:03:20,833 --> 00:03:22,416
WE'RE GOING TO THE HOT SPRINGS.

31
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:24,750
- HOT SPRINGS?

32
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:26,791
IS THAT SO?

33
00:03:26,875 --> 00:03:29,208
- ( horn honks loudly )

34
00:03:33,333 --> 00:03:34,958
- AHH!

35
00:03:35,041 --> 00:03:36,958
THE MOUNTAIN AIR
SURE IS FRESH.

36
00:03:37,041 --> 00:03:38,708
- ( bell rings )
- IT SURE IS.

37
00:03:38,791 --> 00:03:40,833
WE FINALLY MADE IT.
- Taeko: HEY, EVERYONE.

38
00:03:40,916 --> 00:03:42,916
- All: HUH?
- WOULD YOU PLEASE WAIT?

39
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,250
- TAEKO-CHAN?

40
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:46,083
- ( exhales )
HOLD ON.

41
00:03:46,166 --> 00:03:47,208
( yelps )

42
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:54,041
- ARE YOU ALL RIGHT THERE,
MISS TAEKO?

43
00:03:54,125 --> 00:03:55,708
- AHH, I'M FINE.

44
00:03:55,791 --> 00:03:58,083
I'M KINDA USED TO THESE
SORTA THINGS HAPPENING.

45
00:03:58,166 --> 00:04:01,083
- HOLD ON, WHERE THE HECK
ARE THE LUNCH BOXES WE BROUGHT?

46
00:04:01,166 --> 00:04:02,916
- MM?  HUH?

47
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,416
- ( horn honking )

48
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:07,416
- ( Taeko screams )

49
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:09,916
I'M SORRY, EVERYONE.

50
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,916
- Sato:
AND I WANTED TO EAT IT TOO.

51
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,666
- Suzuki:
NOT MUCH WE CAN DO NOW.

52
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:16,000
GUESS WE'LL GIVE UP ON THEM
AND EAT OUT SOMEWHERE.

53
00:04:16,083 --> 00:04:17,625
- Taeko: I'M REALLY SORRY.

54
00:04:17,708 --> 00:04:19,458
- Tina:
HEY, CHEER UP, TAE.

55
00:04:19,541 --> 00:04:20,750
WE'RE HAVING THE WELCOME PARTY

56
00:04:20,833 --> 00:04:22,791
FOR NEW PHOTO CLUB
MEMBERS TODAY.

57
00:04:22,875 --> 00:04:24,416
YOU'RE THE MAIN EVENT, TAE!

58
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:25,875
- Taeko: RIGHT...

59
00:04:27,291 --> 00:04:30,000
- UH, EXCUSE ME, EVERYONE?

60
00:04:30,083 --> 00:04:32,208
- YEAH?  WHAT'S UP, AOI-CHAN?

61
00:04:32,291 --> 00:04:34,875
- IS IT REALLY ALL RIGHT
THAT I COME ALONG?

62
00:04:34,958 --> 00:04:37,875
I'M NOT A MEMBER OF
THE PHOTOGRAPHY CLUB, AFTER ALL.

63
00:04:37,958 --> 00:04:39,125
- IT'S ALL RIGHT.

64
00:04:39,208 --> 00:04:41,125
DON'T YOU WORRY ABOUT
A THING, MISS LANDLORD.

65
00:04:41,208 --> 00:04:43,291
I WOULDN'T HAVE DRAGGED YOU
ALL THE WAY OUT HERE

66
00:04:43,375 --> 00:04:44,708
IF IT WASN'T OKAY.

67
00:04:44,791 --> 00:04:47,958
- YEAH, AND PRETTY GIRLS
ARE ALWAYS WELCOME IN MY BOOK.

68
00:04:48,041 --> 00:04:50,250
- MAN, WISH I WAS
IN YOUR SHOES.

69
00:04:50,333 --> 00:04:52,916
LIVING UNDER THE ROOF
OF A GORGEOUS LANDLORD.

70
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,541
- ( chuckles )

71
00:04:54,625 --> 00:04:58,291
I SEE.  SO THAT'S THE WAY
IT LOOKS IN OTHER PEOPLE'S EYES.

72
00:04:58,375 --> 00:05:00,458
- OH.
YOU ALL CERTAINLY KNOW

73
00:05:00,541 --> 00:05:02,291
HOW TO FLATTER PEOPLE WELL,
DON'T YOU?

74
00:05:02,375 --> 00:05:04,291
- ( all laugh )

75
00:05:06,208 --> 00:05:09,250
- THE AIR REALLY IS
NICE OUT HERE.

76
00:05:09,333 --> 00:05:10,416
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN NICE

77
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:12,250
IF MISS MIYABI COULD HAVE
COME ALONG TOO.

78
00:05:12,333 --> 00:05:13,791
- HMM.

79
00:05:13,875 --> 00:05:15,250
THAT'S TRUE, BUT--

80
00:05:15,333 --> 00:05:17,916
- I WAS ORIGINALLY PLANNING
TO GO WITH LADY AOI

81
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,083
ON THE GETAWAY TOMORROW,
BUT...

82
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:23,583
DUE TO WORK CIRCUMSTANCES,

83
00:05:23,666 --> 00:05:26,875
I AM AFRAID THAT I WILL
HAVE TO PASS THIS TIME AROUND.

84
00:05:26,958 --> 00:05:28,166
THEREFORE,

85
00:05:28,250 --> 00:05:30,625
I'M ASKING YOU TO TAKE
THE BEST OF CARE!

86
00:05:30,708 --> 00:05:34,500
THE BEST CARE OF LADY AOI,
IS THAT UNDERSTOOD?!

87
00:05:34,583 --> 00:05:36,166
IF ANYTHING SHOULD
HAPPEN TO HER

88
00:05:36,250 --> 00:05:39,208
UNDER YOUR WATCHFUL EYE,
SIR KAORU...

89
00:05:39,291 --> 00:05:41,375
- MISS MIYABI SOUNDED LIKE
SHE'D REALLY KILL ME

90
00:05:41,458 --> 00:05:43,625
IF ANYTHING HAPPENED TO YOU.

91
00:05:43,708 --> 00:05:46,041
- Tina: BY THE WAY, TAE...
- Both: HMM?

92
00:05:46,125 --> 00:05:48,708
- ...WHEN THE HECK ARE WE
GONNA FINALLY REACH THE HOTEL?

93
00:05:48,791 --> 00:05:50,208
- I'M NOT SURE.

94
00:05:50,291 --> 00:05:52,625
- BUT DIDN'T YOU SAY THAT
IT WAS NEAR THE TRAIN STATION?

95
00:05:52,708 --> 00:05:54,916
- Tina: TRAIN STATION?
- IF I RECALL,

96
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,583
THE TRAIN STATION SHOULD BE 
SOMEWHERE IN THIS DIRECTION.

97
00:05:57,666 --> 00:05:59,041
- All: HUH?

98
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:00,750
- ( beeping )

99
00:06:00,833 --> 00:06:02,333
- I'M SORRY.

100
00:06:02,416 --> 00:06:04,250
MY SENSE OF DIRECTION'S
NOT SO GOOD.

101
00:06:04,333 --> 00:06:06,583
- YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
WHO KNOWS HOW TO GET THERE,

102
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:08,083
SINCE YOU MADE
THE RESERVATION,

103
00:06:08,166 --> 00:06:10,083
SO GET A GRIP ALREADY,
MINAZUKI.

104
00:06:10,166 --> 00:06:13,416
- RIGHT. THE HOTEL'S CALLED
THE MANOU INN, AND LET'S SEE...

105
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:15,083
LET'S SEE.

106
00:06:15,166 --> 00:06:17,250
OH, I SEE IT NOW.
IT'S THAT WAY.

107
00:06:17,333 --> 00:06:18,583
IF WE TAKE THIS PATH,

108
00:06:18,666 --> 00:06:19,541
IT'LL BE A SHORTCUT.

109
00:06:20,666 --> 00:06:22,125
- ( water rushing )

110
00:06:22,208 --> 00:06:23,458
- UH...

111
00:06:25,583 --> 00:06:27,375
I'M SORRY,
IT'S THIS WAY.

112
00:06:27,458 --> 00:06:29,291
( chuckles nervously )

113
00:06:29,375 --> 00:06:30,583
UH.

114
00:06:30,666 --> 00:06:32,291
- MONKEY REGRET!

115
00:06:32,375 --> 00:06:33,416
- ( laughing )

116
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:35,208
HEY, MR. MONKEY, UP HERE!

117
00:06:35,291 --> 00:06:37,333
- I THINK IT'S OVER HERE.
( nervously chuckles )

118
00:06:41,916 --> 00:06:43,083
- ARE YOU READY, EVERYONE?

119
00:06:43,166 --> 00:06:44,416
- All: CHEESE!

120
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:46,583
- MAY-- MAYBE IT'S OVER
THIS WAY.

121
00:06:46,666 --> 00:06:47,666
- ( all groaning )

122
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:49,958
- OH, NO.

123
00:06:52,541 --> 00:06:54,208
- ( yawns )

124
00:06:54,291 --> 00:06:57,208
JUST WHERE EXACTLY IS THIS HOTEL
WE'RE STAYING AT?

125
00:06:57,291 --> 00:06:59,916
- WE'VE BEEN LOOKING
FOR THREE HOURS.

126
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,916
- OH, I'M SORRY.

127
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,083
- HUH?

128
00:07:03,166 --> 00:07:05,875
AOI-CHAN, ARE YOU DOING OKAY?
- HUH?

129
00:07:05,958 --> 00:07:07,708
I AM PERFECTLY FINE.

130
00:07:07,791 --> 00:07:09,958
THANK YOU VERY MUCH
FOR YOUR CONCERN, KAORU-SAMA.

131
00:07:10,041 --> 00:07:11,291
- GOOD TO HEAR.

132
00:07:13,875 --> 00:07:16,750
AOI-CHAN LOOKS SO SMALL
AND FRAIL.

133
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:20,333
BUT SHE MIGHT BE
STRONGER THAN I THOUGHT.

134
00:07:20,416 --> 00:07:22,166
- Taeko:
I'M SORRY!  I'M SORRY!

135
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:24,333
EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED
WAS MY FAULT.

136
00:07:24,416 --> 00:07:26,958
- TAEKO-CHAN, HOLD ON.
IF THE STATION'S THERE

137
00:07:29,916 --> 00:07:32,041
AND THIS IS THE MAIN STREET,

138
00:07:32,125 --> 00:07:33,625
AND THE HOTEL IS AT
THE END OF THE STREET...

139
00:07:34,791 --> 00:07:35,708
UH--

140
00:07:35,791 --> 00:07:37,625
- All: AAH!

141
00:07:37,708 --> 00:07:39,375
- ( bell tolls )

142
00:07:39,458 --> 00:07:42,791
- Kaoru: I WAS WONDERING WHAT
WOULD HAPPEN FOR A WHILE THERE.

143
00:07:42,875 --> 00:07:44,291
- DESPITE IT ALL,

144
00:07:44,375 --> 00:07:46,250
IT'S STILL GOOD THAT
WE FOUND THE HOTEL.

145
00:07:46,333 --> 00:07:47,750
- MAN, I'M BEAT.

146
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:50,916
I WANNA GET TO THE HOT SPRINGS
PRONTO AND START RELAXING.

147
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,541
- Taeko: WHAT?!
- All: HUH?

148
00:07:52,625 --> 00:07:54,500
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN
 YOU DON'T SEE IT?

149
00:07:54,583 --> 00:07:56,666
- I'M SORRY.
AS I ALREADY SAID,

150
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:58,666
THERE'S NO RESERVATION
UNDER THAT NAME.

151
00:07:58,750 --> 00:08:00,541
- THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

152
00:08:00,625 --> 00:08:02,541
I'M SURE THAT I MADE
A RESERVATION.

153
00:08:02,625 --> 00:08:04,875
IT'S THE MEIRITSU UNIVERSITY
PHOTO CLUB.

154
00:08:04,958 --> 00:08:07,458
- SO YOU SAY,
BUT IT'S NOT HERE.

155
00:08:07,541 --> 00:08:09,625
- IT COULDN'T BE THAT
YOU MADE THE RESERVATION

156
00:08:09,708 --> 00:08:11,875
FOR NEXT MONTH, COULD IT?
TAE?

157
00:08:11,958 --> 00:08:13,208
- YOU KNOW WHAT, TINA?

158
00:08:13,291 --> 00:08:15,250
EVEN IF WE ARE
TALKING ABOUT TAEKO-CHAN,

159
00:08:15,333 --> 00:08:16,416
I DON'T THINK THAT SHE WOULD--

160
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:18,458
- OH, IT MUST BE 
THIS RESERVATION.

161
00:08:18,541 --> 00:08:20,291
IT'S MADE FOR THIS DAY
NEXT YEAR.

162
00:08:20,375 --> 00:08:21,750
- AAH!

163
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:23,750
- NO-- NO WAY.

164
00:08:23,833 --> 00:08:26,666
- EXCUSE ME, ARE THERE ANY
AVAILABLE ROOMS NOW?

165
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:29,500
- UNFORTUNATELY,
WE'RE BOOKED SOLID TONIGHT.

166
00:08:29,583 --> 00:08:32,291
AND THERE HAVEN'T BEEN
ANY CANCELLATIONS EITHER.

167
00:08:32,375 --> 00:08:34,750
- ISN'T THERE ANYTHING THAT
YOU COULD DO FOR US?

168
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:37,416
- I'M AFRAID THAT
THERE REALLY ISN'T.

169
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:39,750
- KAORU-SAMA.

170
00:08:39,833 --> 00:08:40,916
( slightly gasps )

171
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:43,416
- LADY AOI,
IF YOU HAVE ANY PROBLEMS,

172
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:46,541
THEN PLEASE,
USE THIS V.I.P. CARD.

173
00:08:46,625 --> 00:08:49,500
MOST CORPORATIONS WILL DO
SOMETHING IF YOU HAVE THIS.

174
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:52,875
- ( all groan )

175
00:08:52,958 --> 00:08:56,333
- I'M SORRY.
- WHAT NOW...?

176
00:08:56,416 --> 00:08:59,958
- PARDON ME, ANY ROOM YOU
HAVE WOULD BE ACCEPTABLE.

177
00:09:00,041 --> 00:09:01,666
ISN'T THERE ANY WAY?

178
00:09:01,750 --> 00:09:05,000
- AS I SAID EARLIER,
WE'RE BOOKED SOLID--

179
00:09:05,083 --> 00:09:06,083
HUH?

180
00:09:06,166 --> 00:09:08,208
ISN'T-- ISN'T THIS...

181
00:09:08,291 --> 00:09:10,375
( stammering )
GE-- GET A ROOM THIS INSTANT!

182
00:09:10,458 --> 00:09:12,333
- Man: HUH, BUT AREN'T
WE BOOKED SOLID?

183
00:09:12,416 --> 00:09:14,500
- JUST DO IT!
- YES, SIR!

184
00:09:14,583 --> 00:09:16,458
- ( running footsteps )
- ( clears throat )

185
00:09:16,541 --> 00:09:18,791
I AM TERRIBLY SORRY.

186
00:09:18,875 --> 00:09:21,958
WE WILL HAVE A ROOM
PREPARED FOR YOU MOMENTARILY.

187
00:09:22,041 --> 00:09:24,458
- I THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

188
00:09:24,541 --> 00:09:25,750
- AOI-CHAN.

189
00:09:25,833 --> 00:09:28,291
- THIS IS GREAT NEWS,
ISN'T IT?

190
00:09:28,375 --> 00:09:30,583
- THANKS FOR THE SAVE.

191
00:09:30,666 --> 00:09:33,000
WE CAN STAY.

192
00:09:33,083 --> 00:09:34,916
AOI-CHAN HERE
TALKED THEM INTO IT.

193
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,291
- ALL RIGHT!

194
00:09:36,375 --> 00:09:38,458
- THANK YOU SO MUCH, MISS AOI.

195
00:09:38,541 --> 00:09:40,791
- YOU'RE SOMETHING ELSE,
MISS LANDLORD.

196
00:09:40,875 --> 00:09:42,166
- EH, WAS NOTHING.

197
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:45,166
AFTER ALL,
THIS IS THE FIRST TIME

198
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:47,125
THAT KAORU-SAMA AND I WILL--

199
00:09:47,208 --> 00:09:48,958
- ( knocking )

200
00:09:50,833 --> 00:09:53,041
- Tina:
AHH, IF THIS ISN'T HEAVEN,

201
00:09:53,125 --> 00:09:55,041
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IS.

202
00:09:55,125 --> 00:09:57,333
NOTHING'S BETTER THAN
SOAKING IN THE HOT SPRINGS

203
00:09:57,416 --> 00:09:59,000
AFTER A HARD DAY.

204
00:09:59,083 --> 00:10:00,541
- YEAH, BUT...
( sighs )

205
00:10:00,625 --> 00:10:03,041
IF IT WEREN'T
FOR WHAT I DID...

206
00:10:03,125 --> 00:10:05,000
- Aoi: WHAT'S THE MATTER,
MISS TAEKO?

207
00:10:05,083 --> 00:10:07,666
- MISS AOI.

208
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:09,833
I AM REALLY SUCH
A KLUTZ, YOU KNOW.

209
00:10:09,916 --> 00:10:13,500
I JUST SEEM TO CAUSE TROUBLE
FOR ALL OF THE PEOPLE AROUND ME.

210
00:10:13,583 --> 00:10:15,708
( deeply sighs )
LIKE TODAY.

211
00:10:15,791 --> 00:10:20,250
I'M JUST THE TYPE OF PERSON 
WHO CAN'T DO ANYTHING RIGHT.

212
00:10:20,333 --> 00:10:22,291
- I DON'T THINK
THAT'S TRUE AT ALL.

213
00:10:22,375 --> 00:10:24,916
MISS TAEKO.
- MISS AOI.

214
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,583
- DO YOUR BEST,

215
00:10:26,666 --> 00:10:29,750
AND SOMEONE WILL ALWAYS BE THERE
TO ACKNOWLEDGE THAT EFFORT.

216
00:10:29,833 --> 00:10:32,291
AND THAT'S TRUE
FOR THE BOTH OF US.

217
00:10:32,375 --> 00:10:35,083
THAT'S WHY
I ALWAYS DO MY BEST

218
00:10:35,166 --> 00:10:37,291
THINKING ABOUT
THAT PARTICULAR PERSON.

219
00:10:37,375 --> 00:10:39,250
I CAN DO MY BEST

220
00:10:39,333 --> 00:10:41,250
EVEN IN DIFFICULT SITUATIONS

221
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:43,916
WHEN I IMAGINE
THAT PERSON'S HAPPINESS.

222
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:47,083
SO, YOU SHOULD DO
YOUR BEST AS WELL TOO.

223
00:10:47,166 --> 00:10:49,750
I'M SURE YOU CAN,
IF I COULD DO IT.

224
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:52,208
YOU KNOW I'LL BE
ROOTING FOR YOU.

225
00:10:52,291 --> 00:10:54,375
- THANKS A LOT, MISS AOI.

226
00:10:54,458 --> 00:10:58,041
- HEY, WHAT'S WITH
THE LONG FACES OVER THERE?

227
00:10:58,125 --> 00:11:00,125
WE'RE ON A GETAWAY, AFTER ALL.

228
00:11:00,208 --> 00:11:02,750
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO BE HAVING
ALL THE FUN WE CAN.

229
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:03,875
RIGHT?

230
00:11:03,958 --> 00:11:05,375
- RIGHT!

231
00:11:05,458 --> 00:11:06,875
- Suzuki: ALL RIGHT!

232
00:11:06,958 --> 00:11:09,791
WE CAN'T CALL IT A GETAWAY
IF WE DON'T HAVE A PARTY!

233
00:11:12,166 --> 00:11:13,750
- HEY, THERE!

234
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:15,916
- WE'VE ALREADY STARTED.

235
