AND A RIVER ALONG THE WAY HERE.

384
00:17:57,375 --> 00:17:59,291
IF WE WERE TO STRAY
FROM THE PATH,

385
00:17:59,375 --> 00:18:01,958
THERE'S A POSSIBILITY
THAT WE COULD END UP IN DANGER.

386
00:18:02,041 --> 00:18:05,458
- YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.
LET'S WAIT FOR THE FOG TO CLEAR.

387
00:18:05,541 --> 00:18:09,333
- I HOPE THAT MISS TINA AND THE
OTHERS ARE NOT WORRIED ABOUT US.

388
00:18:09,416 --> 00:18:11,291
- ( bell dings )
- ( all snoring loudly )

389
00:18:16,750 --> 00:18:19,500
- WHAT'S THIS?
TAEKO-CHAN'S ASLEEP ALREADY.

390
00:18:19,583 --> 00:18:22,500
- SHE MUST HAVE BEEN
VERY TIRED.

391
00:18:22,583 --> 00:18:24,958
- YEAH, LOOKS THAT WAY.

392
00:18:25,041 --> 00:18:26,125
- ( shivering )

393
00:18:26,208 --> 00:18:27,791
- ARE YOU COLD?

394
00:18:27,875 --> 00:18:30,083
- NO.  OHH.

395
00:18:30,166 --> 00:18:32,666
I FEEL RELIEVED NOW,
BUT...

396
00:18:32,750 --> 00:18:34,000
- HUH?

397
00:18:34,083 --> 00:18:35,958
- ACTUALLY,
TO TELL THE TRUTH,

398
00:18:36,041 --> 00:18:39,666
IT WAS REALLY FRIGHTENING FOR ME
TO COME ALL THE WAY OUT HERE.

399
00:18:39,750 --> 00:18:42,000
- THEN WHY'D YOU
 PUT UP WITH IT?

400
00:18:42,083 --> 00:18:45,000
- WELL, IT'S BEEN
MY DREAM LATELY

401
00:18:45,083 --> 00:18:47,916
TO GO ON A GETAWAY
WITH YOU, KAORU-SAMA.

402
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,583
- I GET IT.

403
00:18:49,666 --> 00:18:51,333
- ( inaudible )
- ( slow piano melody playing )

404
00:18:51,416 --> 00:18:53,000
- THE REASON
SHE LOOKED COMPOSED

405
00:18:53,083 --> 00:18:55,375
WASN'T BECAUSE 
SHE WAS STRONG,

406
00:18:55,458 --> 00:18:57,250
BUT BECAUSE SHE WAS
GOING OUT OF HER WAY

407
00:18:57,333 --> 00:18:59,875
TO KEEP ME FROM
WORRYING ABOUT HER.

408
00:18:59,958 --> 00:19:02,958
THE REAL AOI-CHAN WAS
ACTUALLY...

409
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:05,333
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
DON'T WORRY ANYMORE.

410
00:19:05,416 --> 00:19:07,458
- I'M SORRY.

411
00:19:11,166 --> 00:19:13,041
OH.  OH.

412
00:19:14,625 --> 00:19:15,875
WHAT SHOULD I DO?

413
00:19:15,958 --> 00:19:17,958
I CAN'T SEEM
TO STOP TREMBLING.

414
00:19:18,041 --> 00:19:19,666
- MM.

415
00:19:19,750 --> 00:19:23,375
AOI-CHAN?
- YES?

416
00:19:23,458 --> 00:19:25,333
( exhales )

417
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,750
KA-- KAORU-SAMA?

418
00:19:28,833 --> 00:19:31,083
- YOUR TREMBLING,
IT STOPPED.

419
00:19:31,166 --> 00:19:32,916
- OH.

420
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:33,875
( gasps )

421
00:19:35,875 --> 00:19:37,458
- ( chuckles )

422
00:19:37,541 --> 00:19:39,625
- YOU'RE RIGHT.

423
00:19:39,708 --> 00:19:41,458
IT MOST CERTAINLY HAS.

424
00:19:41,541 --> 00:19:43,458
- ( both chuckle softly )

425
00:19:56,083 --> 00:19:56,958
- KAORU-SAMA?

426
00:20:00,958 --> 00:20:02,166
- AOI-CHAN!
- HUH?

427
00:20:07,041 --> 00:20:08,791
- GOOD MORNING.

428
00:20:08,875 --> 00:20:10,333
COME ON OVER HERE.

429
00:20:12,166 --> 00:20:14,083
- ( exhales )
SURE.

430
00:20:21,125 --> 00:20:22,875
THIS IS...

431
00:20:22,958 --> 00:20:25,833
- SEE?  IT'S BEAUTIFUL,
DON'T YOU THINK?

432
00:20:25,916 --> 00:20:28,666
- YES.  AMAZING.

433
00:20:28,750 --> 00:20:30,625
- ( soft flute music playing )

